    "body": "Sometimes the vim.pack tests fail on Windows ci:\n\n```\nERROR    test/functional/plugin/pack_spec.lua @ 415: vim.pack after_each\nvim/fs.lua:735: EBUSY: resource busy or locked: D:/a/neovim/neovim/build/Xtest_xdg_plugin/share/nvim-data/site/pack/core/opt/plugindirs\n\nstack traceback:\n\tvim/fs.lua:735: in function 'rm'\n\tvim/fs.lua:722: in function 'rm'\n\tvim/fs.lua:764: in function 'rm'\n\ttest/functional/plugin\\pack_spec.lua:416: in function <test/functional/plugin\\pack_spec.lua:415>\n```\n\nThis can happen because Windows doesn't allow file/dir deletion if the process has a handle to it.\n\nWorkaround is to use `n.rmdir()` : https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/53038d2c381e79fcb2ba9c7c5b2e637e3db76f6a/test/functional/testnvim.lua#L842",
